, Italy","Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Caradoc","type":"LAST","meanings":["English: The English form of the British name Caradwg."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Owain","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Perhaps derived in the Roman period from the Latin name <i>Eugenius</i> (  see  <b>Eugene</b>   ); alternatively, possibly from an Old Celtic name meaning ‘born of Esos’. Esos (or Aesos) was a Celtic god known to have been the subject of a cult in ancient Gaul."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Owain Ap Caradoc was born in 1302, his father, Caradoc ap Gwilym, was 28 and his mother, Joan Ferch OWAIN, was 31. He had at least 2 daughters with Lleucu Gwyn ferch Einion Sais. He died in 1365, in Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 63, and was buried in Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1302–1365":"1302–1365","–Female":"Surnud","1302–1320":"1302–1320","1347–Female":"1347–Surnud","1354–Female":"1354–Surnud","1275–1326":"1275–1326","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1326":"1326","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","Abt 1365":"umbes 1365","1354":"1354","1365":"1365","1320":"1320","Abt 1326":"umbes 1326","1275":"1275","1272":"1272","Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales","of Glyntawe, Defynnog, Breconshire, Wales":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Glyntawe, Defynnog, Breconshire, Wales":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","{Blddn ap Mnrch}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia","Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1302–1365":"1302–1365","–Female":"Kuollut","1302–1320":"1302–1320","1347–Female":"1347–Kuollut","1354–Female":"1354–Kuollut","1275–1326":"1275–1326","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1326":"1326","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","Abt 1365":"noin 1365","1354":"1354","1365":"1365","1320":"1320","Abt 1326":"noin 1326","1275":"1275","1272":"1272","Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Abergavenny, Monmouthshire, Wales","of Glyntawe, Defynnog, Breconshire, Wales":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glyntawe, Defynnog, Breconshire, Wales":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Ranska","{Blddn ap Mnrch}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Italia","Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glyntawe, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1302–1365":"1302–1365","–Female":"Décédée","1302–1320":"1302–1320","1347–Female":"1347–Décédée","